main event: Two round, circular objects were observed moving at a very fast speed over Red Bluff, California on August 19, 1952.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be a white, fuzzy light and made no sound.
The objects were observed for 10 seconds, heading south at an estimated altitude of 5,222 feet.
The observer was located approximately 2 miles north of Red Bluff, California.
The report was evaluated as 'probably balloon'.
The Air Technical Intelligence Center at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base acknowledged receipt of the report and stated that a technical evaluation was in progress.
